⚙️ Methodology
1️⃣ Data Preprocessing
Removed missing values
Filtered invalid transactions
Created TotalPrice feature
2️⃣ RFM Analysis
Recency → Days since last purchase
Frequency → Number of purchases
Monetary → Total spending

👉 Customers categorized based on purchasing behavior

3️⃣ Feature Scaling
Applied StandardScaler to normalize RFM features
4️⃣ K-Means Clustering
Used Elbow Method to find optimal clusters
Segmented customers into:
High Value
Mid Value
Low Value
5️⃣ Cluster Analysis
Revenue contribution per cluster
Customer distribution
Spending patterns

👉 Identified key business segments

6️⃣ CLTV (Customer Lifetime Value)
Estimated customer value using:
CLTV = Average Purchase Value × Purchase Frequency
Segmented customers into:
High CLTV
Mid CLTV
Low CLTV
7️⃣ 🤖 Customer Strategy Engine (CORE FEATURE)

Built a rule-based system that assigns business strategies to each customer based on:

Cluster (behavior)
CLTV (value)
💡 Strategy Types
Segment Type	Strategy
High Value + High CLTV	💎 VIP Retention
Mid Value + High CLTV	📈 Upsell Opportunity
Mid Value	🤝 Customer Nurturing
Low Value + Low CLTV	🔄 Re-engagement
Others	📣 General Marketing
📊 Output

Each customer is enriched with:

RFM metrics
Cluster label
CLTV value
CLTV segment
✅ Recommended Strategy
